18 NaN \nThe Pahadia Mandir and Sarovar, Varanasi\nThe Pahadia Mandir is next to a Sarovar. It is a Shiva Mandir and best of all it has a functional Akhara. Not the harmful gym type but the original akhara where you can wrestle, lift weights, and wield the Gada.\r\n Great Place.\r\n\r\n \nAkharas in the Hindu Tradition\n\r\n Akharas have been part of Mandirs since ages, especially Hanuman Mandirs. Most Mandirs in Varanasi used to have attached Akharas especially the ones\r\n near the Ganga Ghats. The various Veer Mandirs around Varanasi had the same tradition.\r\n Nag Panchami used to be the great festival when the Akharas would organize fights and people in the locality\r\n would attend.\r\n Its dying out.Nag Panchami is not even a school holiday in Varanasi now.\r\n \nRevised on 22-Sep-2019 by Champak Roy\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPahadia Mandir Bell\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPahadia Mandir Compound Detail.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPahadia Mandir Compound Detail.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPahadia Mandir Front and Bell, Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPahadia Mandir Bell\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPahadia Mandir Shikhar.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPahadia Mandir Side Detail.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPahadia Mandir, Devi, Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN

It is a Shiva Mandir and best of all it has a functional Akhara. Not the harmful gym type but the original akhara where you can wrestle, lift weights, and wield the Gada.\r\n Great Place.\r\n\r\n \nAkharas in the Hindu Tradition\n\r\n Akharas have been part of Mandirs since ages, especially Hanuman Mandirs. Most Mandirs in Varanasi used to have attached Akharas especially the ones\r\n near the Ganga Ghats. The various Veer Mandirs around Varanasi had the same tradition.\r\n Nag Panchami used to be the great festival when the Akharas would organize fights and people in the locality\r\n would attend.\r\n Its dying out.Nag Panchami is not even a school holiday in Varanasi now.\r\n \nRevised on 22-Sep-2019 by Champak Roy\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPahadia Mandir Bell\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPahadia Mandir Compound Detail.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPahadia Mandir Compound Detail.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPahadia Mandir Front and Bell, Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPahadia Mandir Bell\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPahadia Mandir Shikhar.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPahadia Mandir Side Detail.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPahadia Mandir, Devi, Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nTo see more images please click here\n\n\n\n\nMap of Shri Pahadia Mandir area, Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCONTACT\n\n\nContact us for any query about Varanasi and we'll get back to you within 24 hours.\n Varanasi, India\n +91 9335874326\n varanasikshetra@gmail.com\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSend\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nÂ©Champak's World\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN

3 \r\n Rishi Kardam is one of the Prajapatis created by Brahma Ji. Bhrigu, Marichi,\r\nAtri, Daksha, Kardam, Pulastya, Pulaha, Angira and Kratu are some of the Prajapatis.\r\n\r\nRishi Kardam and Dharma were created from the shadow of Bhagwan Brahma.\r\n\r\nBrahma created Rishi Marichi from his eyes, Rishi Bhrigu came from his heart.\r\nRishi Angira came from his head,Rishi Pulaha from his Vyan Vayu and Rishi Pulatsya from his Udana Vaya.\r\n\r\nRishi Vashishtha the Rajguru of Ayodhya came from his Samana Vayu. Rishi Kratu from his Apan Vayu.\r\nAtri Rishi descended from the ear of Brahma.\r\nNarada came from the lap of Brahma. Another Prajapati was Daksha.\r\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN
4 \r\n Brahma Ji ordered Rishi Kardam to tapasya and accordingly the Rishi undertook Tapasya.\r\n After this Rishi Kardam was married to Devahuti the daughter of Manu and Shatrupa. Rishi Kardam and Devahuti were the first couple to undertake creation in the earthly way.\r\n The Rishi couple had nine daughters.These were Kala, Anusuya, Shraddha, Havirbhu, Gati, Shanti, Krita,Khyati and Arundhati.\r\n\r\n The daughters were married off. Kala to Marichi,Anusuya to Atri, Shradha to Angira, Havirbhu to Pulasatya, Gati to Pulah, Shanti to Atharva, Krita to Kratu,Khyati to Bhrigu, and Arundhati to Vasistha.\r\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN

The Shikhara of this Mandir is the only one that survived the Islamic and British Invasions.\r\nKardameshwar Mahadev is a must visit.\r\n\r\n \nCreation of Rishi Kardam and the other Prajapatis.\n\r\n Rishi Kardam is one of the Prajapatis created by Brahma Ji. Bhrigu, Marichi,\r\nAtri, Daksha, Kardam, Pulastya, Pulaha, Angira and Kratu are some of the Prajapatis.\r\n\r\nRishi Kardam and Dharma were created from the shadow of Bhagwan Brahma.\r\n\r\nBrahma created Rishi Marichi from his eyes, Rishi Bhrigu came from his heart.\r\nRishi Angira came from his head,Rishi Pulaha from his Vyan Vayu and Rishi Pulatsya from his Udana Vaya.\r\n\r\nRishi Vashishtha the Rajguru of Ayodhya came from his Samana Vayu. Rishi Kratu from his Apan Vayu.\r\nAtri Rishi descended from the ear of Brahma.\r\nNarada came from the lap of Brahma. Another Prajapati was Daksha.\r\n\n\nMarriage and children of Rishi Kardam\n\r\n Brahma Ji ordered Rishi Kardam to tapasya and accordingly the Rishi undertook Tapasya.\r\n After this Rishi Kardam was married to Devahuti the daughter of Manu and Shatrupa. Rishi Kardam and Devahuti were the first couple to undertake creation in the earthly way.\r\n The Rishi couple had nine daughters.These were Kala, Anusuya, Shraddha, Havirbhu, Gati, Shanti, Krita,Khyati and Arundhati.\r\n\r\n The daughters were married off. Kala to Marichi,Anusuya to Atri, Shradha to Angira, Havirbhu to Pulasatya, Gati to Pulah, Shanti to Atharva, Krita to Kratu,Khyati to Bhrigu, and Arundhati to Vasistha.\r\n \nShri Kapila Muni the son of Rishi Kardam and Devi Devahuti\n\r\n Shri Vishnu himself took birth as the son of the Rishi couple.Kapila Muni preached Adhyatma Yoga to his mother Mata Devahuti. Rishi Kardam took sanyas leaving aside the grihastha ashram.\r\n \nRevised on 09-Sep-2019 by Champak Roy\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir, Mata Mandir\nMata Mandir\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir,Mata Mandir detail.\nMurti detail\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir Rudrashtakam, Varanasi\nKardameshwar Mandir. first stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir Sarovar, Varanasi\nKardameshwar Mandir Sarovar\n\n\n\n\n\nTo see more images please click here\n\n\n\n\nMap of Shri Kardameshwar Mahadev Mandir area, Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN

14 NaN \nThe Kardameshwar Mandir, Varanasi\nThe Kardameshwar Mandir is the first stop of the Pachkoshi pilgrimage. The oldest surviving Mandir in Varanasi. The Shikhara of this Mandir is the only one that survived the Islamic and British Invasions.\r\nKardameshwar Mahadev is a must visit.\r\n\r\n \nCreation of Rishi Kardam and the other Prajapatis.\n\r\n Rishi Kardam is one of the Prajapatis created by Brahma Ji. Bhrigu, Marichi,\r\nAtri, Daksha, Kardam, Pulastya, Pulaha, Angira and Kratu are some of the Prajapatis.\r\n\r\nRishi Kardam and Dharma were created from the shadow of Bhagwan Brahma.\r\n\r\nBrahma created Rishi Marichi from his eyes, Rishi Bhrigu came from his heart.\r\nRishi Angira came from his head,Rishi Pulaha from his Vyan Vayu and Rishi Pulatsya from his Udana Vaya.\r\n\r\nRishi Vashishtha the Rajguru of Ayodhya came from his Samana Vayu. Rishi Kratu from his Apan Vayu.\r\nAtri Rishi descended from the ear of Brahma.\r\nNarada came from the lap of Brahma. Another Prajapati was Daksha.\r\n\n\nMarriage and children of Rishi Kardam\n\r\n Brahma Ji ordered Rishi Kardam to tapasya and accordingly the Rishi undertook Tapasya.\r\n After this Rishi Kardam was married to Devahuti the daughter of Manu and Shatrupa. Rishi Kardam and Devahuti were the first couple to undertake creation in the earthly way.\r\n The Rishi couple had nine daughters.These were Kala, Anusuya, Shraddha, Havirbhu, Gati, Shanti, Krita,Khyati and Arundhati.\r\n\r\n The daughters were married off. Kala to Marichi,Anusuya to Atri, Shradha to Angira, Havirbhu to Pulasatya, Gati to Pulah, Shanti to Atharva, Krita to Kratu,Khyati to Bhrigu, and Arundhati to Vasistha.\r\n \nShri Kapila Muni the son of Rishi Kardam and Devi Devahuti\n\r\n Shri Vishnu himself took birth as the son of the Rishi couple.Kapila Muni preached Adhyatma Yoga to his mother Mata Devahuti. Bhrigu, Marichi,\r\nAtri, Daksha, Kardam, Pulastya, Pulaha, Angira and Kratu are some of the Prajapatis.\r\n\r\nRishi Kardam and Dharma were created from the shadow of Bhagwan Brahma.\r\n\r\nBrahma created Rishi Marichi from his eyes, Rishi Bhrigu came from his heart.\r\nRishi Angira came from his head,Rishi Pulaha from his Vyan Vayu and Rishi Pulatsya from his Udana Vaya.\r\n\r\nRishi Vashishtha the Rajguru of Ayodhya came from his Samana Vayu. Rishi Kratu from his Apan Vayu.\r\nAtri Rishi descended from the ear of Brahma.\r\nNarada came from the lap of Brahma. Another Prajapati was Daksha.\r\n\n\nMarriage and children of Rishi Kardam\n\r\n Brahma Ji ordered Rishi Kardam to tapasya and accordingly the Rishi undertook Tapasya.\r\n After this Rishi Kardam was married to Devahuti the daughter of Manu and Shatrupa. Rishi Kardam and Devahuti were the first couple to undertake creation in the earthly way.\r\n The Rishi couple had nine daughters.These were Kala, Anusuya, Shraddha, Havirbhu, Gati, Shanti, Krita,Khyati and Arundhati.\r\n\r\n The daughters were married off. Kala to Marichi,Anusuya to Atri, Shradha to Angira, Havirbhu to Pulasatya, Gati to Pulah, Shanti to Atharva, Krita to Kratu,Khyati to Bhrigu, and Arundhati to Vasistha.\r\n \nShri Kapila Muni the son of Rishi Kardam and Devi Devahuti\n\r\n Shri Vishnu himself took birth as the son of the Rishi couple.Kapila Muni preached Adhyatma Yoga to his mother Mata Devahuti. Rishi Kardam took sanyas leaving aside the grihastha ashram.\r\n \nRevised on 09-Sep-2019 by Champak Roy\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir, Mata Mandir\nMata Mandir\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir,Mata Mandir detail.\nMurti detail\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir Rudrashtakam, Varanasi\nKardameshwar Mandir. first stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\nKardameshwar Mandir Sarovar, Varanasi\nKardameshwar Mandir Sarovar\n\n\n\n\n\nTo see more images please click here\n\n\n\n\nMap of Shri Kardameshwar Mahadev Mandir area, Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCONTACT\n\n\nContact us for any query about Varanasi and we'll get back to you within 24 hours.\n Varanasi, India\n +91 9335874326\n varanasikshetra@gmail.com\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSend\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nÂ©Champak's World\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN

It is the holiest city for Hindus. It is the Avimukta Kshetra where Purusha and Prakriti dwelt first. Varanasi is Shiva KShetra. It was a Vishnu KShetra before. \r\n Varanasi is settle next to the left banks of the Ganga and numerous Ghats line up their. Varanasi is also the dwelling place of Shiva where he lives as the Vishweshwar Linga in the Kashi Viswanath Mandir at Gyanvapi.\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe Assi River\nThe Assi River flows into the Ganga at the famous Assi Ghat. 0 NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN VaranasiKshetra.com: The Kashi Panchkoshi Parikrama Kshetra is the Avimukta Kshetra.Its the part of Varanasi that lies within the Panchkoshi Parikrama Marg.Hindus undertake a Parikrama Yatra on this road on MahaShivratri. Approximately 75kms, the yatra begins at the Manikarnika Ghat, then Shri Kardameshwar Mahadev, Devi Bheem Chandi, Rameshwar Mahadev, Pancha Pandava, and Kapil Dhara. \r\nThen the yatris go to Jau Vinayak and a steamer takes them back to Manikarnika.\r\nWomen undertake a 5 days Parikrama in the month of Malmas. 19 NaN \n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe Assi River\nThe Assi River flows into the Ganga at the famous Assi Ghat. The Assi Ghat is famous as the dwelling place of Goswami Tulsidas ji.\r\n The Ramacharita Manas was composed here. The Assi Ghat is famous for the early morning Kirtans and cultural activities. The Ganga Aarti takes place here.\r\n The Assi River flows next to the Baba Kinarama Asthal. It is the holiest city for Hindus. It is the Avimukta Kshetra where Purusha and Prakriti dwelt first. Varanasi is Shiva KShetra. It was a Vishnu KShetra before. \r\n Varanasi is settle next to the left banks of the Ganga and numerous Ghats line up their. Varanasi is also the dwelling place of Shiva where he lives as the Vishweshwar Linga in the Kashi Viswanath Mandir at Gyanvapi.\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe Assi River\nThe Assi River flows into the Ganga at the famous Assi Ghat. The Assi Ghat is famous as the dwelling place of Goswami Tulsidas ji.\r\n The Ramacharita Manas was composed here. The Assi Ghat is famous for the early morning Kirtans and cultural activities. The Ganga Aarti takes place here.\r\n The Assi River flows next to the Baba Kinarama Asthal. The river has unfortunately been polluted beyond recognition by sewers emptying into it.\r\n Efforts are being made to revive it.\r\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\nPlaces in Varanasi\n\n\n\n\nBheem Chandi\nBheem Chandi,Rameshwar\n\n\n\n\n\nRameshwar Mahadev Mandir on the Varuna\nThird stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama\n\n\n\n\n\nKapil Dhara, Varanasi\nLast stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama Yatra\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nBhairav Nath Mandir.\nOn the Rajatalab to Jansa Road\n\n\n\n\n\nPancha Pandava Mandir, Varanasi\n fourth stop on the Kashi Panchkoshi parikrama.\n\n\n\n\n\nKapil Dhara, Varanasi\nFifth and last stop on the Panchkoshi parikrama\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nMap of Varanasi\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCONTACT\n\n\nContact us for any query about Varanasi and we'll get back to you within 24 hours.\n Varanasi, India\n +91 9335874326\n varanasikshetra@gmail.com\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSend\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nÂ©Champak's World\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n NaN NaN NaN NaN NaN
